Convolution means:

Applying a small filter (kernel) over input data to extract important features.

============


A Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is a type of 
deep learning model mainly used for processing images and other grid-like data (like videos or spectrograms). 
It’s widely used in computer vision tasks such as image classification, object detection, and facial recognition.

===============

What makes CNNs special?

Unlike regular neural networks, CNNs are designed to automatically detect important features (like edges, shapes, textures) 
from raw input—without manual feature engineering.

===============
| Step | Layer                 | Purpose                                                      |
| ---- | --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| 1    | Input Image           | Original image is given to the CNN model                     |
| 2    | Convolution           | Extracts important features like edges, shapes, and patterns |
| 3    | ReLU Activation       | Removes negative values and adds non-linearity               |
| 4    | Pooling               | Reduces image size and keeps important information           |
| 5    | Convolution           | Detects more complex features from previous layers           |
| 6    | Pooling               | Further reduces dimensions and computation                   |
| 7    | Flatten               | Converts 2D feature maps into a 1D vector                    |
| 8    | Fully Connected Layer | Learns relationships between extracted features              |
| 9    | Output Prediction     | Predicts the final class (e.g., digit 0–9)                   |


==================

