================

8️⃣ Output Layer

Final output nodes:

0 → 9

The CNN predicts which digit is present.

Example:

Highest probability = 7
Output prediction = digit “7”

=================

Why CNN is Powerful Here

Compared to ANN:

CNN automatically extracts image features
ANN treats every pixel independently
CNN preserves spatial relationships

That’s why:

ANN accuracy may stay around 20–40%
CNN can achieve 95–99% accuracy on image tasks

================

The word “Convolutional” in Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) comes from the mathematical operation called Convolution.

Meaning of “Convolution”
-------------------------

Convolution means:

Applying a small filter (kernel) over input data to extract important features.

In CNN:

A small matrix called a filter/kernel moves across the image.
It checks small regions one by one.
It detects patterns like:
edges
curves
textures
shapes

===================

Simple Example

Suppose we have an image:

🟦🟦🟦
🟦⬛🟦
🟦🟦🟦

A filter slides over the image and identifies:

vertical lines
horizontal lines
corners

This sliding operation is called Convolution.

Why the Name “Convolutional Neural Network”?

Because the network mainly uses:

Convolution operations
through Convolution Layers

So it is called:

Convolutional Neural Network

===================


Simple Real-Life Analogy
-----------------------

Imagine:

You are reading a newspaper using a magnifying glass.
You scan small areas one at a time.
You identify letters and patterns.

CNN does the same with images using filters.
===================

In Short

| Term          | Meaning                                                 |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| Convolution   | Sliding filter operation to detect features             |
| Convolutional | Using convolution operations                            |
| CNN           | Neural network specialized for image feature extraction |


